File and Directory Commands

ls              # List files
ls -l            # Long list
ls -a            # Show hidden files
pwd              # Current directory
cd /path         # Change directory
mkdir dir        # Create directory
rmdir dir        # Delete empty directory
rm -r dir        # Delete directory
touch file       # Create file
cp src dest      # Copy file
mv src dest      # Move / rename

File Viewing and Editing

cat file         # View file
less file        # Scroll view
head file        # First 10 lines
tail file        # Last 10 lines
tail -f file     # Live logs
nano file        # Edit file
vi file          # Edit with vim


Search and Text Processing 

grep word file               # Search word
grep -i word file            # Case-insensitive
grep -r word dir             # Recursive search
sed 's/old/new/g' file       # Replace text
awk '{print $1}' file        # Print column


Permission and Ownership

chmod 755 file               # Change permissions
chmod +x script.sh           # Make executable
chown user:group file        # Change owner
ls -l                        # View permissions


User and Group Management

useradd teja                 # Add user
passwd teja                  # Set password
userdel teja                 # Delete user
groupadd devops              # Add group
groups teja                  # Check groups


Process Management

ps -ef                       # All processes
top                          # Live processes
htop                         # Enhanced top
kill PID                     # Kill process
kill -9 PID                  # Force kill


Networking Commands

ip a                         # IP address
ping google.com              # Check connectivity
netstat -tulnp               # Open ports
ss -tulnp                    # Modern netstat
curl url                     # HTTP request
wget url                     # Download file


Disk and Memory

df -h                        # Disk usage
du -sh dir                   # Directory size
free -h                      # Memory usage
lsblk                        # Block devices
mount                        # Mounted filesystems

